SplunkGate — Agentic AI Safety
==============================

Runtime AI agent safety net for Splunk + Cisco enterprises.

Version: 1.0.0
Author: SplunkGate Project
License: Apache-2.0

Supported Splunk versions: 9.4, 10.0, 10.1, 10.2, 10.3, 10.4
Supported platforms: Splunk Cloud, Splunk Enterprise

What this app does
------------------

Ingests SplunkGate verdicts (emitted via HTTP Event Collector by the
splunkgate_mw Python middleware) under the sourcetype
cisco_ai_defense:splunkgate_verdict — the same namespace populated by
the Cisco Security Cloud Splunkbase app (7404), so SOC analysts see
SplunkGate events next to AI Defense events in their existing search
workflows.

Includes three Dashboard Studio v2 dashboards:

  - Agent Risk Overview — live counters, severity breakdown, blocked
    actions by agent
  - Verdict Inspector — drill-down on individual verdicts with full
    provenance (input text, evaluator chain, latency, OTel trace)
  - Regulator Evidence Pack — PDF-exportable view for examiners,
    with NIST AI RMF function alignment and SR 26-2 framing

Install
-------

Splunk Cloud:
  Apps -> Find more apps -> search "SplunkGate" -> Install
  (Or upload via Splunkbase once the app is published.)

Splunk Enterprise:
  $SPLUNK_HOME/bin/splunk install app /path/to/splunkgate_app.tgz
  $SPLUNK_HOME/bin/splunk restart

After install:
  Settings -> Apps -> SplunkGate -> Set up
  Configure the HEC token your splunkgate_mw middleware emits to so
  the cisco_ai_defense:splunkgate_verdict sourcetype is indexed.

